<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en" lang="en">
<head>
    <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" />
    <title>XHT File Example</title>
</head>
<body>
    <div>
        <h1>XHT File Format</h1>
        <p>Files with the .xht extension are XHTML (eXtensible HyperText Markup Language) documents. XHTML is essentially HTML reformulated as XML, which means it follows stricter syntax rules than traditional HTML.</p>
        <h2>Benefits of XHTML</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Stricter syntax enforcement</li>
            <li>Better compatibility with XML tools</li>
            <li>Improved code quality and maintainability</li>
            <li>Easier validation and error detection</li>
        </ul>
        <p>XHTML files can be served with the MIME type application/xhtml+xml or text/html, depending on the server configuration and browser support.</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

